nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Cytosine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network prioritizes literature-supported surface cyanosulfidic and cyanoacetaldehyde chemistry while using hydrothermal iron-sulfur chemistry to supply shared C1/C2 feedstocks (formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, pyruvate) and biochemical stages to convert assembled pyrimidine nucleotides or nucleosides into free cytosine where relevant. Because free cytosine is hydrolytically unstable, the primary route follows the Powner\u2013Sutherland strategy in which the pyrimidine ring is built on a sugar-phosphate scaffold and cytosine is accessed through cytidine/cytidine-cyclic-phosphate intermediates. Alternative literature-supported branches include cyanoacetaldehyde + urea, cyanoacetylene + cyanate, cyanoacetaldehyde + guanidine, formamide thermolysis on minerals, UV formamide photochemistry on TiO2, frozen NH4CN oligomerization, and meteoritic/interstellar delivery analogs. Hub molecules are HCN, cyanoacetylene, cyanoacetaldehyde, 2-aminooxazole, and cytidine-2',3'-cyclic phosphate.\n\nMOLECULES (28 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H4N2O (2-aminooxazole) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C5H8N2O2 (ribo/arabino aminooxazoline) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3HN (cyanoacetylene) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H5N3O (cytosine) [target]\n  - mol_012: CHNO (cyanate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C3H2N2O (trans-cyanovinylurea) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C3H3NO (cyanoacetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: CH4N2O (urea) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: CH3NO (for