\": 0.7,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.69,\n      \"feedback\": \"Formamide condensation on TiO2 is literature-supported, and cytosine-containing product pools are plausible. However, the reaction is mixture-rich, not selective, and the network treats the pool as too cleanly separable into cytosine. This branch is useful as a documented alternative but should remain lower confidence than the Sutherland and Robertson-Miller routes.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_019\",\n        \"rxn_020\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Specify neat formamide or high-formamide conditions around 160 C with TiO2, matching Saladino et al.\",\n        \"Model the output as a heterogeneous nucleobase mixture rather than a near-direct cytosine source.\",\n        \"Reduce confidence in the isolation/release step unless supported by concentration or partitioning arguments.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.34,\n        \"rxn_019\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_020\": 0.74\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.68,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.73,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.7,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.68,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.68,\n      \"feedback\": \"This branch is similar to P6 but slightly weaker because montmorillonite-supported formamide chemistry is still strongly mixture-forming and less directly diagnostic for cytosine than the best TiO2 cases. It is literature aligned as an alternative route, but not a strong directed synthesis pathway.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_019\",\n        \"rxn_020\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Differentiate catalyst-dependent product distributions between TiO2 and montmorillonite.\",\n        \"Represent cytosine as one component of a wider formamide condensate ou